def: Having a sharp, lean, or thin back; as, a razor-backed hog,perch, etc.

To put a covering about; to wrap up or in; to inclose within acase, wrapper, integument or the like; to surround entirely; as, toenvelop goods or a letter; the fog envelops a ship.Nocturnal shades this world envelop. J. Philips.
The point between the north and east, at an equal distance fromeach; the northeast part or region.
Exasperated; imbittered. [Obs.] Shak.Like swallows which the exasperate dying year Sets spinning. Mrs.Browning.
Of or pertaining to a proctor, esp. an academic proctor;magisterial.
An instrument for measuring currents, especially the force orintensity of electrical currents; a galvanometer.
A crystalline substance closely related to xanthin, present insmall quantity in urine.
A plane of an orthorhombic crystal which is parallel both tothe vertical axis and to the shorter lateral (brachydiagonal) axis.
A low outwork before a bastion or ravelin, consisting of twolines of rampart parallel to the faces of the bastion, and protectingthem from a breaching fire.
Made, or done, with a single color; as, a monochromic picture.
